name: David Lammy
summary: David Lammy, the UK's Foreign Secretary, has taken a series of public stances on various issues. During a visit to Israel, Lammy urged an immediate ceasefire. In a separate incident, he defended his prior labeling of former US President Donald Trump as a "neo-Nazi sociopath." Lammy also met with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to advocate for a Gaza ceasefire. Additionally, Lammy asserted that the UK is not actively pursuing a renegotiation of its trade agreement with the EU. While on his first visit to the Middle East, Lammy called for an immediate ceasefire in Gaza. Lammy has faced criticism from some quarters, including accusations of national embarrassment and problematic past tweets. His stance on Israel has also been subject to examination and debate, with some questioning his views. Moreover, Lammy has expressed his belief that Christianity and class provide a common ground between himself and JD Vance.

name: Heathrow
summary: Multiple news outlets reported on widespread disruptions at Heathrow Airport, the world's fourth busiest airport, due to a global Microsoft IT outage. American Airlines passengers experienced distress when their wheelchair assistance was delayed, while Lily Allen missed her flight home from Heathrow. The outage also caused numerous flight cancellations and delays. Additionally, Heathrow, Gatwick, and Stansted Airports provided updates on the scrapping of the 100ml liquid travel rule. Amidst the chaos, Heathrow extended its partnership with SITA, and SITA announced plans to enhance Heathrow's IT infrastructure. The outage affected over 4,000 flights, causing delays at Heathrow, Stansted, and Gatwick airports.

name: Mason Greenwood
summary: Mason Greenwood's tumultuous time at Manchester United has come to an end, as he has signed a five-year deal with French club Marseille. The move comes after United reached an agreement with the Ligue 1 side for a fee potentially rising to £30 million. Greenwood, who has been suspended by United since allegations of assault and attempted rape surfaced against him in January 2022, has been the subject of intense scrutiny and public backlash. Despite the charges being dropped due to lack of evidence, the signing of Greenwood has sparked controversy in Marseille, where some residents have protested against his arrival. The deal marks a significant departure for United, who had initially stood by Greenwood but later suspended him indefinitely. It is also a major signing for Marseille, who are hoping Greenwood can help them challenge for the Ligue 1 title.
